214
00:11:15,150 --> 00:11:16,030
No.

215
00:11:17,150 --> 00:11:18,120
Hold this for me.

216
00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:19,880
Was Jiang Ting your classmate?

217
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,550
Yes, who are you?

218
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,480
Here's my business card.

219
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:29,670
[Lawyer Lei Shuang]

220
00:11:29,670 --> 00:11:30,870
Ms. Lei.

221
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,320
Can I have a chat with you?

222
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,120
Does it fit?

223
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,240
Yes.

224
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:25,240
When was it made?

225
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,580
You don't come back often.

226
00:12:27,670 --> 00:12:28,450
Your dad

227
00:12:28,670 --> 00:12:30,840
makes one for you

228
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:33,200
now and then.

229
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:36,810
The closet is almost full of the clothes
he made for you.

230
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:43,200
So,

231
00:12:44,550 --> 00:12:45,670
how's his gout?

232
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:48,560
Not much difference.

233
00:12:48,670 --> 00:12:50,390
I told him to drink less every day.

234
00:12:50,390 --> 00:12:51,720
But he wouldn't listen.

235
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:54,480
He often cries in pain at night.

236
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:57,600
We used to be reluctant to
spend much money.

237
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:58,390
Your clothes

238
00:12:58,390 --> 00:13:00,120
were all made by your dad.

239
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:02,110
I remember once

240
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:04,370
a customer brought a designer outfit.

241
00:13:04,490 --> 00:13:06,240
Your dad thought it was very good.

242
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,360
So he made an outfit

243
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,790
in its style for you.

244
00:13:08,910 --> 00:13:10,120
He even stitched an extra rabbit doll
on it.

245
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:10,720
Mom.

246
00:13:11,510 --> 00:13:13,170
Let's not talk about the past.

247
00:13:14,510 --> 00:13:16,870
I think the clothes my dad made for me
are good.

248
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:19,070
Even better than the designer clothes.

249
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:24,120
I'll call your dad

250
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:26,440
to ask when he'll come back.

251
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:32,790
Mrs. Fang, is my outfit ready?

252
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:34,790
Li, you're here.

253
00:13:34,790 --> 00:13:36,400
I've finished tailoring your outfit.

254
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:38,440
This is my daughter, Lingyuan.

255
00:13:38,550 --> 00:13:40,610
She works in the provincial capital.

256
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,000
I didn't know

257
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:53,400
your home is so close to
our glass workshop.

258
00:13:54,630 --> 00:13:56,830
But how come I've never seen you before?

259
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:57,670
It's normal.

260
00:13:58,210 --> 00:14:00,440
I went to college in
the provincial capital.

261
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,320
I've been working there since I graduated.

262
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:03,360
I only come back

263
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:04,790
a few times a year,

264
00:14:05,150 --> 00:14:07,480
It's normal that you've never seen me before.

265
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:08,150
Right.

266
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:10,420
Your job must be very busy.

267
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:13,440
Yes.

268
00:14:14,610 --> 00:14:16,070
That's one of the reasons.

269
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:18,360
And...

270
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:26,500
