00:15:00,550 --> 00:15:03,510
In pursuit of justice, Xie ran after
Person A and Person B.

285
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:06,270
In order to prevent Xie
from overtaking their car,

286
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:08,110
Person A and Person B
drove in a serpentine way.

287
00:15:08,110 --> 00:15:09,030
After a 2-kilometer drive,

288
00:15:09,030 --> 00:15:11,670
their car hit a cement barrier
on the road.

289
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,320
Xie had no time to brake

290
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:15,200
and hit the car of Person A
and Person B.

291
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,750
As a result, Xie got critically injured.

292
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:19,680
This should be a question
on that year's exam, right?

293
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:23,440
I think so.

294
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,000
So,

295
00:15:25,390 --> 00:15:26,590
what was your answer?

296
00:15:27,030 --> 00:15:27,630
I...

297
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:30,480
It was too long ago. I almost forgot it.

298
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:31,320
Let me think.

299
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:39,200
Person A and Person B drove
in a serpentine way,

300
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,750
creating intolerable risks.

301
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:44,150
What they did was dangerous.

302
00:15:44,790 --> 00:15:46,480
And that behavior led to

303
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:47,750
this outcome.

304
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:49,910
So both Person A and Person B

305
00:15:49,910 --> 00:15:51,770
should take the responsibility.

306
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,530
I don't think that's right.

307
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:56,870
In some cases, although the person created

308
00:15:56,870 --> 00:15:58,400
created intolerable risks

309
00:15:58,550 --> 00:16:00,670
and caused the result.

310
00:16:00,790 --> 00:16:02,720
But if the relation between the risks
and result is not

311
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:06,380
within the scope of the effectiveness
of constitutive elements,

312
00:16:06,390 --> 00:16:09,920
the person doesn't need to
take responsibility for the result.

313
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,750
But I think

314
00:16:15,270 --> 00:16:17,930
the fugitive should take
some responsibility.

315
00:16:19,140 --> 00:16:20,600
Let me give you an example.

316
00:16:24,030 --> 00:16:26,270
If a drug seller sold drugs to someone
and the drugs caused the buyer's death,

317
00:16:26,270 --> 00:16:28,120
should the seller

318
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:30,480
be charged with the crime
of negligent homicide?

319
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,470
If a prostitute with a venereal disease

320
00:16:32,470 --> 00:16:34,510
told her customer that she had the disease

321
00:16:34,510 --> 00:16:36,960
but the customer insisted having sex with
the prostitute and then got infected,

322
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:39,000
should the prostitute be charged

323
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,630
with offenses of causing bodily harm?

324
00:16:40,630 --> 00:16:42,150
The drug buyer
and the prostitute's customer

325
00:16:42,150 --> 00:16:45,270
were aware of the risks

326
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:48,200
and were willing to take full responsibility
for the risks.

327
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,930
The risks are self-trap risks.

328
00:16:50,390 --> 00:16:52,250
In the case we discussed just now,

329
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:54,360
the behaviors of Person A and Person B

330
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:56,870
were one of the factors

331
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:58,910
for Xie's serious injury.

332
00:16:59,080 --> 00:16:59,840
Xie was seriously injured

333
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:01,910
mainly because he drove improperly

334
00:17:01,910 --> 00:17:03,790
and caused the rear-ending accident.

335
00:17:03,790 --> 00:17:04,829
So,

336
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:06,720
the responsibility for the result

337
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:08,680
shouldn't be taken by Person A
and Person B.

338
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:09,589
This should be

339
00:17:10,270 --> 00:17:12,400
the standard answer to the question
from that year, right?

340
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,859
You can still memorize it.

341
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:19,680
But more factors need to be taken
into consideration

342
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:21,410
in the actual judgment, right?

343
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:33,000
I didn't know until I became a prosecutor

344
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,000
that the Persons ABCD in those questions

345
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,000
on our test papers

346
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,590
are no longer imaginary figures.

347
00:17:39,310 --> 00:17:41,310
They were real people.

348
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:45,790
So,

349
00:17:47,030 --> 00:17:48,630
when we're working on a case,

350
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:51,480
we can't ignore

351
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:54,280
what the people in the cases
have been through.

